<item>
            <title>[LU-10380] lfs changelog almost always returns EIO</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10380</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running &lt;tt&gt;lfs changelog &amp;lt;device&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; invariably returns EIO and outputs: &lt;em&gt;Changelog: Input/output error&lt;/em&gt;&quot;, unless there aren&apos;t any changelog records to read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appeared after this commit: cd36001b &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10218&quot; title=&quot;errors not propagated to changelog readers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mdc: propagate changelog errors to readers&quot;. I do not know whether the commit introduced a bug or simply highlighted an already existing one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
